prompt_template:
A task requires capabilities not available in existing toolkits.

TASK DESCRIPTION: {{ task_description }}
MISSING CAPABILITY: {{ missing_capability }}
SUGGESTED NAME: {{ toolkit_name }}

EXISTING TOOLKITS:
{% for tk in existing_toolkits %}
- {{ tk.name }}: {{ tk.description }}
{% endfor %}
{% if not existing_toolkits %}(No existing toolkits.){% endif %}

Design a new toolkit module. A toolkit is a Python module containing
classes and functions that provide reusable capabilities. Examples:
- A PDF parsing library with classes for reading, extracting text/tables
- A web access library with functions for fetching URLs, parsing HTML
- A markdown writer library for structured document generation

Respond in this exact JSON:
{
  "name": "...",
  "description": "...",
  "dependencies": ["pip_package_1"],
  "requires_approval": true,
  "public_api": [
    {"name": "ClassName.method_name", "description": "...",
     "params": "...", "returns": "..."}
  ]
}
